OL,3,CMan who stabbed author Salman Rushdie
OL,4,Con stage sentenced to 25 years in
OL,5,Cprison
OL,7,FThe man who stabbed author Salman
OL,8,FRushdie on stage in 2022, leaving him
OL,9,Fblind in one eye, was sentenced on
OL,10,FFriday to 25 years in prison.
OL,12,FHadi Matar, 27, was found guilty in
OL,13,FFebruary of attempted murder and
OL,14,Fassault after attacking Rushdie as he
OL,15,Fwas about to speak at a literary event
OL,16,Fin New York.
OL,18,FHe received the maximum sentence,
OL,19,Falong with a separate seven-year term
OL,20,Ffor injuring another man who was on
OL,21,Fstage at the time.
