OL,7,FIn requesting the maximum sentence,
OL,8,FProsecutor Jason Schmidt told the
OL,9,Fjudge that Matar: "Chose this. He
OL,10,Fdesigned this attack to inflict the
OL,11,Fmost damage, not just on Mr Rushdie,
OL,12,Fbut on this community and the 1,400
OL,13,Fpeople who were there to watch it."
OL,15,FDefence lawyer Nathaniel Barone argued
OL,16,Ffor a 12-year sentence, noting Matar
OL,17,Fhad no prior criminal record and
OL,18,Fquestioning whether the audience
OL,19,Fshould be considered victims.
